From: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
Date: Sat, 04 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qualcomm: ppe: add L3 flow engine accessors

Add the low level accessors of the PPE L3 flow engine, in preparation
for offloading netfilter flowtables.

The flow engine forwards IPv4 5-tuple flows in hardware: packets with
a destination MAC matching the router MAC table take the L3 route
path, and a flow table hit forwards the packet through its next hop
entry, which provides the egress port, the MAC rewrites (destination
from the entry, source from the egress L3 interface) and the egress
VLAN. NAT is expressed the same way: the translated source of an SNAT
flow comes from the public IP table referenced by the next hop, the
translated destination of a DNAT flow from the next hop itself, and
the translated L4 port lives in the flow entry. Flow misses take the
ordinary path to the CPU, so partially offloaded traffic keeps
working.

Flow entries are inserted and deleted through the flow operation
registers, using the combined flow-and-host commands which maintain
the host table entry of the second tuple address together with the
flow, hashed by the hardware. A delete can instead act on the flow
alone, leaving the host entry in place for other flows that share the
destination address. The command protocol matches the FDB operations,
serialized by their own lock. The flow counter table
provides per-flow hit counters.

The hardware ages flows by default (unlike the FDB, where the aging
timer is disabled out of reset): disable the flow aging at init, the
flow table users manage the lifetime of their entries.

Signed-off-by: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
---
